<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏠 M000 Week 5 — English Worksheet (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Roofed House · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 38 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set of steps. Before you imagine the agent doing it, write your answer in your own words.</p>
<pre><code>repeat 4 times:
    repeat 4 times:
        place block down
        move forward
    turn right
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks are placed in total, and what shape do they make on the ground? Explain how you counted.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>move up by 1
repeat 3 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Do the new blocks land at the same height as the walls, or higher? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows clean steps first, then a broken version of the same idea. The goal is given before each pair. Find what changed and explain the bug in one short sentence.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — <em>Goal: place exactly 5 blocks in a row.</em></p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 5 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — <em>Goal: finish one whole straight side, then turn once.</em> Hint: look closely at where <code>turn right</code> sits.</p>
<pre><code># clean
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
turn right
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
repeat 4 times:
    place block down
    move forward
    turn right
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair C</strong> — <em>Goal: rise one block first so the roof sits on top of the walls.</em> Hint: order matters.</p>
<pre><code># clean
move up by 1
place block down
move forward
</code></pre>
<pre><code># buggy
place block down
move forward
move up by 1
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The roof must sit <strong>on top</strong> of the walls, so the agent has to rise before it builds the roof line. One line is missing. Write the missing line, then explain in one sentence why it goes there.</p>
<pre><code>____________
place block down
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>move up by 1</code> · <code>turn right</code> · <code>move forward</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing line:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does that line go first?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your homework world. Build your <strong>roofed house</strong> — any size you like. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your house, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 3 or 4 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>First, I …</p>
<p>Then I used a loop to …</p>
<p>My roof works because …</p>
<p>The hardest part was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + a photo or video of your finished house to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
